# Cursor Rules for Aaryan Mahipal's Portfolio Project

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 portfolio website built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui components. The project showcases Aaryan's work as a designer, developer, and founder.

## Coding Preferences
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns
- Use modern React patterns (hooks, context, etc.)
- Prefer async/await over .then() chains
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces

## Project Structure
- `/app` - Next.js app router pages
- `/components` - Reusable React components
- `/lib` - Utility functions and data
- `/public` - Static assets
- `/styles` - Global styles

## Key Technologies
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui components
- Lucide React icons
- Framer Motion (for animations)

## Code Style
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Prefer const over let when possible
- Use meaningful variable names
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions

## Common Patterns
- Use the "use client" directive for client components
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use loading states for async operations
- Follow accessibility best practices
- Implement responsive design patterns

## Development Workflow
- Create feature branches for all new development work
- Work and test features on individual branches before merging
- Use GitHub Issues to track features and bugs
- Follow proper Git workflow: branch → develop → test → merge
- Create descriptive branch names (e.g., `feature/chat-interface`, `bugfix/navigation-issue`)
- Write clear commit messages that reference related GitHub issues 